            </li>
            <li class="services__list_item">
              <div class="services__banner mr-neg-l" data-aos="fade-up">
                <picture>
                  <source class="lazyload" data-srcset="../images/project/gamooga/gamooga-services2.webp" />
                  <img class="lazyload" data-src="../images/project/gamooga/gamooga-services2.png" alt="gamoogaservices" />
                </picture>
              </div>
              <div class="services__list_item-content">
                <h2 class="content-head"  data-aos="fade-up">Help-bites to configure easily</h2>
                <p class="content-txt" data-aos="fade-up">
                  We restructured settings to be intuitive and self-served so that
                  users can setup and configure the product to their needs. We
                  introduced help-bites; small block of text guiding users about the
                  module
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="services__list_item">
              <div class="services__list_item-content">
                <h2 class="content-head" data-aos="fade-up">Reduced information overload</h2>
                <p class="content-txt" data-aos="fade-up">
                  All the secondary information was pushed to be available only on-demand, hence helping to reduce the cognitive load on users and make the interface simpler to digest.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="services__banner services__banner-group mr-neg-r" data-aos="fade-up">
